<title>CSS Text 7.4. Justification Method: text-justify: inter-character</title>
<link href="mailto:jeremychen@mozilla.com" rel="author" title="Chun-Min (Jeremy) Chen" />
<link href="https://www.mozilla.org" rel="author" title="Mozilla" />
<link href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-text-3/#text-justify-property" rel="help" />
<link href="reference/text-justify-inter-character-001-ref.xht" rel="match" />
<meta content="text-justify:inter-character means justification adjusts spacing between each pair of adjacent typographic character units." name="assert" />
<style type="text/css">
p {
  font-size: 1.5em;
  border: 1px solid black;
  padding: 10px;
  margin-right: 310px;
}
.test {
  text-align-last: justify;
  text-justify: inter-character;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<p lang="en" class="test">XX</p>
<p lang="ja" class="test">文字</p>


</body></html>